According to the [U.S. Census Bureau](/United_States_Census_Bureau), Loudoun County covers 521 square miles (1,350 km 2 ). &#91;17&#93; Most of it is land, a mere 1.1% is water. It hugs the [Potomac River](/Potomac_River) to the north, facing Maryland counties like [Frederick](/Frederick_County,_Maryland), [Washington](/Washington_County,_Maryland), and [Montgomery](/Montgomery_County,_Maryland). To the south are [Prince William](/Prince_William_County,_Virginia) and [Fauquier](/Fauquier_County,_Virginia). To the west, the [Blue Ridge Mountains](/Blue_Ridge_Mountain) mark the border with [Jefferson County, West Virginia](/Jefferson_County,_West_Virginia) and [Clarke County, Virginia](/Clarke_County,_Virginia). And to the east, [Fairfax County](/Fairfax_County,_Virginia). The [Bull Run Mountains](/Bull_Run_Mountains) and [Catoctin Mountain](/Catoctin_Mountain) slice through the county, creating the [Loudoun Valley](/Loudoun_Valley) on the western side. [Short Hill Mountain](/Short_Hill_Mountain) runs through that valley, from [Hillsboro](/Hillsboro,_Loudoun_County,_Virginia) all the way to the [Potomac River](/Potomac_River). It’s a landscape of subtle divisions.

