### Economy

*The shift from rural to… something else.*

Once a quiet, rural place, Loudoun’s population exploded after 1980. It’s now heavily suburbanized, with a full-blown [service economy](/Service_economy). Home to the big players in the internet and [high tech](/High_tech) world: [Verizon Business](/Verizon_Business), [Telos Corporation](/Telos_(defense_company)), [Orbital Sciences Corporation](/Orbital_Sciences_Corporation). [Dulles International Airport](/Dulles_International_Airport) has been a major engine, just like in [Fairfax County's](/Fairfax_County,_Virginia) [Dulles Corridor](/Dulles_Technology_Corridor). &#91;33&#93; &#91;34&#93; &#91; [citation needed](/Wikipedia:Citation_needed) &#93;

But the rural spirit lingers. The [equine](/Equestrianism) industry pulls in $78 million. [Morven Park](/Morven_Park) hosts horse trials. And the wine. Oh, the wine. Loudoun County has 40 [wineries](/Winery) &#91;35&#93; and over 25 active farms. It was once a major [wheat](/Wheat) producer, back in the mid-19th century. &#91;36&#93;

[MCI, Inc.](/MCI,_Inc.), now part of [Verizon Communications](/Verizon_Communications), has its headquarters in [Ashburn](/Ashburn,_Virginia). &#91;37&#93; &#91;38&#93; [AOL](/AOL) used to be here too, in [Dulles](/Dulles,_Virginia). &#91;39&#93; They moved to [New York City](/New_York_City) in 2007, but kept their Virginia offices. &#91;40&#93; [Orbital Sciences Corporation](/Orbital_Sciences_Corporation) is still in Dulles. &#91;41&#93;

And then there are the [data centers](/Data_center). Over 60 of them. &#91;42&#93; &#91;43&#93; They say 70% of global web traffic flows through here. &#91;44&#93; Loudoun County’s "Data Center Alley" is the largest concentration on the planet, with over 25 million square feet. &#91;45&#93; A digital empire built on silicon and fiber.

Before it folded, [Independence Air](/Independence_Air) (formerly [Atlantic Coast Airlines](/Atlantic_Coast_Airlines)) was headquartered in Dulles. &#91;46&#93; &#91;47&#93; [MAXjet Airways](/MAXjet_Airways) was also based at [Dulles International Airport](/Dulles_International_Airport). &#91;49&#93;

