### Government and politics

*The shifting sands of power.*

Many Loudoun County historical structures pre-date the [American Civil War](/American_Civil_War)

For decades, from 1952 to 2008, Loudoun was reliably [Republican](/Republican_Party_(United_States)). But something changed. The [Democrats](/Democratic_Party_(United_States)) started winning, especially after 2014. Now, the [Board of Supervisors](/Board_of_supervisors) is heavily Democratic, and so is the School Board. The constitutional offices, though, still lean Republican. It’s a county that reliably picks the statewide winner in presidential elections, though. A true [bellwether](/Bellwether).

The motto, "I Byde My Time," &#91;2&#93; &#91;51&#93; comes from the [coat of arms](/Coat_of_arms) of the [Earl of Loudoun](/Earl_of_Loudoun). In the latter half of the 20th century, as people moved south from the North, Loudoun swung Republican. They hadn’t voted for a Democratic president since [Lyndon B. Johnson](/Lyndon_B._Johnson) in 1964, until [Barack Obama](/Barack_Obama) in 2008.

That suburban boom in the east, filled with educated professionals commuting to [Washington, D.C.](/Washington,_D.C.), has re-shaped the county’s political landscape. Obama took nearly 54% in 2008. Then [Bob McDonnell](/Bob_McDonnell) won the county in 2009 with 61%. Two Democratic delegates were ousted. In 2012, Obama won again, this time with 51.5% against [Mitt Romney](/Mitt_Romney). &#91;52&#93; Democrats have held the county in presidential elections ever since.

In 2020, [Joe Biden](/Joe_Biden) secured 61.5% of the vote, the best for a Democrat since 1964. &#91;53&#93; And in 2021, [Terry McAuliffe](/Terry_McAuliffe) took the county with 55.3% against [Glenn Youngkin](/Glenn_Youngkin). &#91;54&#93; It was one of the few counties McAuliffe won in Northern Virginia, though his margin was slim. &#91;55&#93; Then, in 2024, [Kamala Harris](/Kamala_Harris) won 56%, but the county shifted right by 9 percentage points compared to 2020. &#91;56&#93; It’s a constant dance, this political pendulum.

