The [National Transportation Safety Board](/National_Transportation_Safety_Board) has an office in [Ashburn](/Ashburn,_Virginia). &#91;65&#93; And the [Federal Aviation Administration](/Federal_Aviation_Administration)'s [Washington Air Route Traffic Control Center](/Washington_Air_Route_Traffic_Control_Center) is in Leesburg, the second busiest in the nation. &#91;66&#93; Always busy, always managing the chaos.

Emergency services are handled by the [Loudoun County Combined Fire and Rescue System](/Loudoun_County_Combined_Fire_and_Rescue_System). A mix of volunteers and paid staff. &#91;67&#93; Law enforcement is primarily the [Loudoun County Sheriff's Office](/Loudoun_County_Sheriff%27s_Office), the largest in Virginia, plus three town police departments. &#91;68&#93; &#91;69&#93; &#91;70&#93; &#91;71&#93;

The [Loudoun County Public Library](/Loudoun_County_Public_Library) system has eleven branches. &#91;72&#93; They’ve won awards. &#91;73&#93; &#91;74&#93;

Loudoun County is one of the few in Virginia that participates in the Virginia Mortgage Assistance Program (VMAP) for its employees. &#91;75&#93; Trying to keep housing affordable for civil servants. A noble effort, I suppose.

### Transportation

#### Airports

Aerial view of [Dulles International Airport](/Dulles_International_Airport) in [Dulles](/Dulles,_Virginia) in August 2024

Two airports: [Dulles International](/Dulles_International) and [Leesburg Executive](/Leesburg_Executive_Airport). Gates to the outside world.

