### Education

*The future, molded.*

The county is served by [Loudoun County Public Schools](/Loudoun_County_Public_Schools) (LCPS). Over 70,000 students. &#91;76&#93; &#91;77&#93; They’ve been recognized for educational achievement relative to spending. &#91;78&#93; They also have the [Loudoun Academy of Science](/Loudoun_Academy_of_Science), now part of the [Academies of Loudoun](/Academies_of_Loudoun), &#91;79&#93; and can send students to [Thomas Jefferson High School for Science and Technology](/Thomas_Jefferson_High_School_for_Science_and_Technology) in [Alexandria, Virginia](/Alexandria,_Virginia). &#91;80&#93;

Ten private schools call Loudoun home: [Loudoun Country Day School](/Loudoun_Country_Day_School), [Notre Dame Academy](/Notre_Dame_Academy_(Middleburg,_Virginia)), [Evergreen Christian School](/Evergreen_Christian_School), [Foxcroft School](/Foxcroft_School), Dominion Academy, Loudoun Classical School, &#91;81&#93; St. Theresa School, Village Montessori School at Bluemont, Christian Faith & Fellowship School, and Loudoun School for Advanced Studies.

Higher education is also present: [Patrick Henry College](/Patrick_Henry_College), [Northern Virginia Community College](/Northern_Virginia_Community_College) (Sterling), [George Washington University](/George_Washington_University), [George Mason University](/George_Mason_University), [Marymount University](/Marymount_University), [Shenandoah University](/Shenandoah_University), and [Strayer University](/Strayer_University) all have satellite campuses. &#91;82&#93; There’s also a campus of the [Virginia–Maryland College of Veterinary Medicine](/Virginia%E2%80%93Maryland_College_of_Veterinary_Medicine) and the [Janelia Farm Research Campus](/Janelia_Farm_Research_Campus) of the [Howard Hughes Medical Institute](/Howard_Hughes_Medical_Institute). &#91; [citation needed](/Wikipedia:Citation_needed) &#93;

